Merry Christmas from the Harrises’🎄

First Christmas married, last year just the two of us ✨

2022 recap - one of the best years of our lives ✨

Every year, I try to scroll back to the very first day of the year and relive its wonderful memories. I write this for myself so I can look back one day and remember all the things that has happened in my life year by year. Started off the New Year by kissing the love of my life Bruce Harris who is now my HUSBAND!! having the best time with my girls in Jamaica for my bachelorette, to bamboo rafting on the Martha Brae river, to getting all muddy ATV-ing with my friends, to eating jerk chicken everyday while in Jamaica, to drinking rum til we drop while partying on a catamaran with my afterlife crew, to holding a sea urchin with my bare hands, to horseback riding in the water, to laughing nonstop with my friends while jumping on a trampoline with pornstars hahaha, to walking up, jumping off, sliding down and ziplining through waterfalls in Ocho Rios, to having a bridal dance battle at a beach party, to dressing up in different colored wigs for brunch, to wedding dress fittings, to ice skating on a lake, to annual family Harris trips to Great Gorge, to GETTING MARRIED in Sedona, to spending our honeymoon in Hawaii, to eating spam musubis everyday, to driving down the road to Hana, to getting drenched at the blowholes of Nakalele, to whale watching in Maui, to walking the red sand beach of Kaihalulu, to eating at mama’s fish house the same place where my husband’s parents also ate at on their honeymoon, to hopping on the back of a local’s truck to get to the green sand beach of Papakolea (which is 1 out of 4 in the world), to eating a donut at the southernmost bakery in the US, to reaching the “real” southernmost point in the US not Key West lol, to visiting our second black sand beach (first one was in Greece), to watching a luau, to seeing the biggest manta rays in the wild —>

Have you ever looked at a photo and wish you can re-live that moment over and over again? 🤍

This is what happens every time I look at our wedding pictures. Can’t believe this was 10 months ago!

100 months 🤍

We were just figuring life out when we first got together. It’s crazy to think how much our lives have changed over the years…how much we’ve grown and learned and experienced together. I know that no matter which direction we end up going in, we will always make sure we are headed there together because we are a team. I am so excited for this next phase in our lives and I cannot wait to see you as a dad, @bruceharris8

365 days since we said I do 💍

If someone told me 8 years ago when we met that you were going to be my husband I wouldn’t have believed them. We met at a time when we both weren’t really looking, yet we still managed to find each other and now 8 years later here we are…

We have had the craziest 365 days - from getting married, to going into full house renovation mode and finding out 5 months later we’re having a baby! I don’t think you could cram in anymore than we did in a year! lol. 

Happy first year wedding anniversary, baby 🤍
soaking up every last second ♥︎

This babymoon has been both a celebration of the life that is to come as we become a family of three and also a chance to soak up the last moments of it being just us two. It has just been me and you for over eight years. It’s all that I know and I have loved and cherished every single moment of it. I love you. I love being two, but I absolutely cannot wait to be three ✨

Baby shower of my dreams ☁️

Feeling a lot of love surrounding baby Harris 🤍 

Thank you to my amazing friends and family for helping me put this baby shower together!

Our baby is so loved already and we are so grateful to have each and everyone of you in our baby’s life.

You make life better in every way possible and I’m soooo excited to see you become a father 🤗

It’s MAY! 💐

Baby’s birth month has finally arrived. I just can’t believe how quick time went by. Mommy and daddy cannot wait to meet you baby! 💕
We’re ready for you angel 🕊️#duedate

On May 19, 2023 at 3:13 am our lives became complete 🤍

Bryson Craig Harris
8 lbs 1 oz
20 inches
The new dad walk 🥰 #dischargedfromthehospital #goinghome #newparents #newmom #newdad #dadwalk #postpartum

I can’t believe it’s been a week since this little cutie pie came into the world. This last week has been the happiest and also has been the most challenging days of our lives. We are exhausted and we can’t help but second guess everything we do but at the same time we also can’t believe we made this tiny perfect human. 👣
Postpartum means matching outfits 🧷 #2weeksold

Watching you become a dad has been one of the best things that I have ever experienced in my life. 

My heart is so full. I didn’t think I could love you more than I already do after all these years, but seeing you with Bryson this past month has made me fall in love with you even more. 🥹

Happy First Father’s Day, baby. 👨‍👩‍👦

Birthday Girl 🎂

Can’t believe it’s been a year since we announced to the world that we were having a baby. I remember feeling all sorts of emotions when we found out I was pregnant, wondering what it would feel like holding you in my arms or what you would look like… and now here we are a year later standing at the same exact spot where we took a picture when you were still in my belly and now we’re both holding you in our arms. 
I just love watching you grow but at the same time I wish I could just stop time and keep you this age forever. Life is so much better with you in it Bryson 🧡 

Thank you for making my first birthday as a mommy extra special. We love you SO much! 🥹

Starting off the new year right ✨

Here’s a recap of how my year went in 2023: 

Every year, I try to scroll back to the very first day of the year and relive its wonderful memories. I write this for myself so I can look back one day and remember all the things that has happened in my life year by year. 

Started off the New Year by kissing the love of my life Bruce Harris, to winning money at the casino for the first day of the year, to traveling to Colombia, to salsa dancing in Getsemani, to watching sunsets on top of an ancient wall that surrounds the city of Cartagena, to shopping for emeralds, to having mud baths inside a volcano, to trying Colombian coffee, to dancing with the palenquera ladies in the plaza while balancing a fruit bowl on my head, to going on a sponsored trip to the Catskills, to taking pregnancy photoshoots, to having lunch inside an old train car, to celebrating our one year wedding anniversary and babymoon in Dominican Republic, to drinking endless virgin coco locos, to celebrating St. Patrick’s day by the beach, to dancing in foam parties, to eating breakfast with storks, to hand rolling Dominican cigars, to having a surprise baby shower at work, to having my “on the cloud” themed baby shower and being with family and friends, TO GIVING BIRTH to my beautiful baby -  Bryson Craig Harris, to spending Memorial Day bbq-ing with friends, to dipping our toes at the beach in the Hamptons, to our first family road trip from NY to VA, to exploring Richmond, to
visiting the St. John’s church where Patrick Henry said “give me liberty or give me death”, to celebrating Bruce’s first Father’s Day, to going to the Mattituck strawberry festival, to going on carousel rides in Greenport, to my first baby collab Sollybaby (1/4)

Spent the whole week in Florida for the first week of the year 🌊

Travel days are not over once you have a kid. They definitely look different and it sure is not for everyone but we love it. Here’s to the start of our 2024 adventures!
